 South Africa has a total of 52 991 confirmed Covid-19 cases according to an announcement by the minister of health, Dr. Zweli Mkhize, on Tuesday, June 9. A total of 184 of those cases have been recorded in Mpumalanga. According to data released by the Mpumalanga Department of Health, 111 recoveries have been recorded to date. There has been one Covid-19 related death recorded in Mbombela, Mpumalanga. • Bushbuckridge: 3 cases and 3 recoveries
• City of Mbombela: 44 cases, 24 recoveries, and one death
• Nkomazi: 24 cases and 21 recoveries
• Thaba Chweu: 9 cases and 4 recoveries • Chief Albert Luthuli: 3 cases and 1 recovery
• Dipaliseng: 0 cases
• Dr Pixely Ka Isaka Seme: 17 cases and 17 recoveries
• Govan Mbeki: 34 cases and 18 recoveries
• Lekwa: 9 cases and 2 recoveries
• Mkhondo: 1 case and no recoveries
• Msukaligwa: 1 case and 1 recovery • Dr JS Moroka: 1 case and 1 recovery
• Emakhazeni: 2 cases and 2 recoveries
